## Section-by-Section Deep Revision

### Hero: Unchanged Core, Refined Details

The "conversation graveyard" concept from the initial strategy remains the strongest hero approach. But with the full feature list in hand, we can make the floating conversation fragments more specific and more emotionally resonant.

**The conversation fragments should include recognizable scenarios:**

```
"Can you help me debug this React hydration error?" — ChatGPT, 3 months ago
"What's the best way to structure a seed pitch deck?" — Claude, 6 weeks ago  
"Explain the difference between HNSW and IVF indexes" — Gemini, 2 months ago
"Write a bedtime story about a dragon who's afraid of fire" — ChatGPT, last week
"Help me plan a 10-day trip through Japan" — DeepSeek, 4 months ago
"Review this pull request for security issues" — Claude, yesterday
```

The mix matters. Include technical, creative, personal, and professional conversations. Every visitor should see at least one fragment that mirrors their own AI usage. The provider labels (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, DeepSeek) immediately communicate multi-provider support without a feature bullet point.

**After the animation resolves (conversations organize into a searchable grid), add a subtle detail:** small colored dots next to each conversation indicating the provider (green for ChatGPT, orange for Claude, blue for Gemini, etc.). This color-coding system should be consistent across the entire site—it becomes part of the visual language.

**The headline refinement:**

```
Before animation:  "Your best ideas are trapped in 9 different apps."
After animation:   "What if they weren't?"
Sub-headline:      "VIVIM captures every AI conversation you've ever had.
                    Search them. Share them. Own them."
```

The shift from "disappearing" (initial strategy) to "trapped" is intentional. "Trapped" implies the conversations still exist but are inaccessible—which is technically accurate and creates a stronger rescue narrative. "9 different apps" directly references the 9-provider capture capability without listing them.

