## The Overarching Narrative

With all the context now integrated, the website tells this story in roughly 3 minutes of scrolling:

**Second 0-5:** *"Your AI conversations are trapped and scattered."* (Hero animation)

**Second 5-10:** *"VIVIM captures all of them, from every provider, into one searchable archive."* (Hero resolution + headline)

**Second 10-60:** *"Try it yourself."* (Interactive demo — capture, search, knowledge graph, sharing)

**Second 60-65:** *"Ready to own your AI intelligence?"* (Post-demo CTA — highest-intent moment)

**Second 65-90:** *"Here's how it works under the hood."* (Context engine, social layer, provider grid — the visitor chooses their depth)

**Second 90-120:** *"Developers: build on top of this."* (SDK, API, plugins, self-hosting)

**Second 120-150:** *"Here's why you can trust us."* (Crypto stack, open source, pricing, portability)

**Second 150-180:** *"Here's where we're going."* (Roadmap, vision statement)

**Final frame:** *"Join us."* (Footer CTA with three paths: waitlist, GitHub, Discord)

Every visitor gets the first 65 seconds. What they explore after the CTA depends on who they are and what they care about. The site respects their autonomy while ensuring the core story—your AI conversations deserve a home—reaches everyone.
